[SPEAKER_00] Hrvatske, da je bilo potrebno potrebno, a da je bilo potrebno, a da je bilo potrebno, a da je bilo potrebno, a da je bilo potrebno, a da je bilo potrebno potrebno, a da je bilo potrebno zaprebno se, da je bilo potrebno.

1080
02:02:43,619 --> 02:03:05,680
[SPEAKER_00] Problem awareness, i think there is something going on in Europe, also to a certain extent, perhaps help by developments outside Europe, which make Europe a worthwhile project and which make in principle also Europe delivering and contributing to growth and welfare in Europe.

1081
02:03:05,899 --> 02:03:20,859
[SPEAKER_00] And that is then something which is a positive symbol. At first it was seen as a threat to developments outside of Europe, but now they are seen as an opportunity. We talk about intensifying European integration, we are talking about deepening monetary union.

1082
02:03:20,859 --> 02:03:40,760
[SPEAKER_00] You see now all these studies which have raised problem awareness and policy makers react to this. The only challenge I still see is that a lot of these developments which are very promising are requiring change.

1083
02:03:40,859 --> 02:03:55,539
[SPEAKER_00] And people don't like change. And then there are others who promise you don't have to change. On the contrary, when you get rid of all these recipes, we can promise you gold at the end of the rainbow.

1084
02:03:55,539 --> 02:04:13,220
[SPEAKER_00] And then, of course, when people like the European Union, European institutions, I wouldn't say we have come up with blood, sweat and tears speeches, but at least we come up with recommendations which are not everywhere greeted with applause.

1085
02:04:13,220 --> 02:04:34,979
[SPEAKER_00] And then others come, you don't have to do this. Relax, we will get everything under control. Then we have, of course, a very difficult stance. And that is then where we also would need support from those who have the deep knowledge and who have the understanding and who have perhaps somewhat longer term perspective and say, okay, we have to go for this structural adjustment.

1086
02:04:34,979 --> 02:04:59,979
[SPEAKER_00] We have to go for this to a certain extent. I wouldn't say creative destruction, but there is creation. And that is then where we come to startups. That what I said to someone, we have a lot of challenges in Croatia with respect to activity rates, productivity, investing in research and development, inefficiency of public sector and health reform, pension reform.

1087
02:04:59,979 --> 02:05:22,979
[SPEAKER_00] But when you then tell that deliver, that is not something which is a threat, that is an opportunity to improve. Others have perhaps already reached the highest level of pension reform. You can still do something. And as a result of this, there is a catching up. And as a result of this, you have a real convergence. So from that point of view, yes, I'm optimistic.

1088
02:05:22,979 --> 02:05:48,840
[SPEAKER_09] Hvala vam ljepa. Iza kraj, gospođo Maletić, evo, vi ste i zastupnica IPP-a i HDZ-a u Europskom parlamentu. Dakle, imate utjecaja, s obzirom da su to najbrojnije političke grupacije, utjecaja zapravo na stvaranje trendova. Čuli ste što bi se zapravo to od nas tražilo? Vjerujem da se i slažete većim dijelom s time. Kako 2018. učiniti upravo tom prijelomnom godinom?

1089
02:05:48,979 --> 02:06:16,560
[SPEAKER_08] Pa, na razini Europske unije, znači će biti definitivno prijelomna godina, jer su u toj godini predviđene najintenzivnije rasprave vezane uz budućnost financiranja Europske unije, jačanje monetarne i ekonomske unije, socijalni pilar, odnosno socijalna politika, o kojoj se raspravlja, obravbena politika. Znači, definitivno se dinamizira jako.

1090
02:06:16,979 --> 02:06:24,420
[SPEAKER_08] I sve rasprave idu u tom smjeru. Kako će, naravno, se voditi velika bitka za kohezijsku politiku?

1091
02:06:24,420 --> 02:06:37,180
[SPEAKER_08] Mislim da sve države članice, pa posebno Hrvatska, moraju pokazati korisnice kohezijske politike, moraju pokazati da imaju taj dobar miks ekonomskih politika,

1092
02:06:37,180 --> 02:06:47,199
